<h2>Races</h2>
<svg width="600" height="500"></svg>
<script src='https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/Chart.js/2.9.3/Chart.min.js'></script>
<canvas id="raceChart" width="400" height="400"></canvas>
<script>
    let backgroundColors = [];
    let borderColors = [];
    for(let i = 1; i<[{{{races}}}].length + 1; i++){
        backgroundColors.push('rgba(' + Math.floor(Math.random()*256).toString() + ', ' + Math.floor(Math.random()*256).toString() + ', ' + Math.floor(Math.random()*256).toString() + ', 0.2');
        borderColors.push('rgba(' + Math.floor(Math.random()*256).toString() + ', ' + Math.floor(Math.random()*256).toString() + ', ' + Math.floor(Math.random()*256).toString() + ', 1');
    }
var ctx = document.getElementById('raceChart').getContext('2d');
var myChart = new Chart(ctx, {
    type: 'bar',
    data: {
        labels: ['Human', 'Elf', 'Gnome', 'Half-Orc', 'Tiefling', 'Halfling', 'Half-Elf', 'Dwarf', 'Aasimar', 'Other'],
        datasets: [{
            label: 'Races',
            data: [{{{races}}}],
            backgroundColor: backgroundColors,
            borderColor: borderColors,
            borderWidth: 1
        }]
    },
    options: {
        responseive: false,
        scales: {
            yAxes: [{
                ticks: {
                    beginAtZero: true
                }
            }]
        }
    }
});
</script>
<p>
    Pathfinder and Dungeons & Dragons on the outside are very similar games. They are both D20 based fantasy RPGs, and Pathfinder is even based on the mechanics of Dungeons & Dragons 3.5 (5 is the current version). On a gameplay level, however, they differ greatly. Pathfinder
    is more compelx that Dungeons & Dragons, both in its play and its character creation. Even with their differences, there are bound to be similarities between the two games, and with this race chart we can see that both games share Humans and Aasimar being the most popular races.
    I would assume that the Aasimar race is played in Pathfinder much for the same reasons as Dungeons & Dragons, but in Pathfinder there are many more options to expand on a players Aasimar power fantasy. There are more classes, feats, and overall options given to players in
    Pathfinder that might give new, more interesting ways to play Aasimar.
</p>
